OL,6,FIn court, his lawyer argued that
OL,7,FBradley had a drug addiction and was
OL,8,Fpressured into participating in the
OL,9,Fraid by people he feared.
OL,11,FBradley's sentence will run
OL,12,Fconcurrently with his existing prison
OL,13,Fterm, and he has also been ordered to
OL,14,Fpay a #187 surcharge.
